&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;As an OSIsoft/AVEVA PI Engineer at Data Systems Analysts, you will be part of a growing business offering at the intersection of energy management, advanced analytics, and cybersecurity. As part of your work, you will actively translate customer requirements into functional and technical designs. You will participate in designing and implementing projects that provide situational awareness and operational intelligence using the OSIsoft/AVEVA PI System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;DSA&#39;s CIP team delivers value by integrating diverse operational systems onto a common data platform while deploying advanced analytics to improve efficiency, resiliency, and mission effectiveness. Within the CIP team, you will regularly work with and integrate data from Building Automation Systems (BAS), Industrial Control Systems (ICS), Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) systems, Advanced Metering Infrastructure (AMI), and other third-party systems into the PI System. You will leverage PI Asset Framework (AF), PI Analytics, PI Vision, and related reporting tools to support data analysis, validation, and operational insights. Our group supports customers across government, utilities, higher education, pharmaceuticals, manufacturing, and other critical infrastructure sectors. As a systems integration team, we focus on delivering measurable value to our customers&#39; missions through scalable, reliable, and secure data solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The majority of your time will be customer facing and project focused. We are seeking a motivated U.S. resident who is comfortable operating in both technical implementation and customer consulting environments. Targeted training will be provided to support continued professional growth; however, candidates should possess a solid hands-on foundation with the PI System and be capable of contributing independently within the first 1 to 3 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The successful candidate will support the design, implementation, and maintenance of new PI System integration projects while also providing operational support for existing environments. Responsibilities include solution design, system integration, PI administration, troubleshooting data collection and interface issues, monitoring system health, supporting customer requests, maintaining PI infrastructure, and assisting with system upgrades and enhancements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Approximately &lt;strong&gt;60-70%&lt;/strong&gt; of the role will focus on customer-facing solution design, implementation, and project delivery, while &lt;strong&gt;30-40%&lt;/strong&gt; will focus on PI System administration, troubleshooting, operational support, and maintenance activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The ideal candidate enjoys systems integration, has a customer-first mindset, takes ownership of technical challenges, and is eager to continuously learn new technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
